This paper discusses the challenges of generating effective training datasets for machine learning models in the context of cybersecurity, indicating a focus on security and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper describes a cloud infrastructure for generating datasets, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the complexity of labeling and concept drift, which suggests a focus on data science (cs.DS).
